  "texts": [
    "Because of this, some of the focus has been shifted onto cost functions that have gradients that do not vanish completely.",
    "Boundary equilibriumThis equilibrium was proposed by GAN (BEGAN) (Berthelot et al., 2017) which identifies the connection between the generator and discriminator losses.",
    "BEGAN has a basic design and showed impressive performance.",
    "It was demonstrated by BEGAN that it is essential for the performance of GANs to strike a balance between two units D and G. The BEGAN architecture, on the other aspect, does not have a structure that is like that of other GANs, hence its applicability is limited.",
    "BEGAN made use of an architecture based on EBGAN (Zhao et al., 2016), which employs as a discriminator, an auto encoder utilizes pixel-wise mean squared loss."
